{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WoFrzyu76juReUuXXD1E4x","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've read both files. Here's a comprehensive summary:\n\n## File Contents Summary\n\n### **chain.ts** — Key Components\n\n**Program ID & Constants (Lines 19-27)**\n- `COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID`: Loads from `VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID` env var, falls back to `CoinflipIDL.address`\n- `ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID`: Hardcoded to `VRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y`\n\n**PDA Derivation (Lines 31-61)**\n- `getMatchPda(creator)`: Seeds = `[\"match\", creator.toBuffer()]`\n- `getConfigPda()`: Seeds = `[\"coinflip_config\"]`\n- `getOraoNetworkStatePda()`: Seeds = `[\"orao-vrf-network-configuration\"]`\n- `getOraoRandomnessPda(seed)`: Seeds = `[\"orao-vrf-randomness-request\", seed]`\n\n**Program Instance (Lines 65-73)**\n```typescript\nfunction getCoinflipProgram(connection: Connection): Program<Coinflip> {\n  const provider = new AnchorProvider(connection, {} as AnchorProvider[\"wallet\"], { commitment: \"confirmed\" });\n  return new Program(CoinflipIDL as Idl as Coinflip, provider);\n}\n```\n\n**OnChainMatch Type (Lines 81-96)** — Raw on-chain account structure:\n```typescript\ninterface OnChainMatch {\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  opponent: PublicKey;\n  tier: number;\n  entryAmount: { toNumber(): number };\n  creatorSide: number;\n  phase: RoundPhaseVariant; // { waiting: {} } | { active: {} } | { locked: {} } | { resolving: {} } | { settled: {} } | { refunded: {} }\n  result: number;\n  winner: PublicKey;\n  claimed: boolean;\n  createdAt: { toNumber(): number };\n  lockedAt: { toNumber(): number };\n  resolveDeadline: { toNumber(): number };\n  vrfRequestKey: PublicKey;\n  bump: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Conversion Logic (Lines 100-163)** — `onChainMatchToUI()`:\n- Converts tier index → tier name (`tierFromIndex`)\n- Converts side index → coin side (`sideFromIndex`)\n- Converts phase variant → UI phase (`phaseToUI`):\n  - `waiting` → `created`\n  - `locked` → `ready`\n  - `settled` → `complete`\n- Calculates payout: `totalPool * 0.97` (where totalPool = `entryAmount * 2`)\n- Checks if opponent exists via `isDefaultPubkey()` check\n\n**Fetch Functions (Lines 167-211)** — No memcmp filters:\n- `fetchAllOpenMatches()`: Loads all accounts, filters in-memory by `isPhase(..., \"waiting\")`\n- `fetchMatchByCreator(creator)`: Direct fetch by derived PDA\n- `fetchMatch(matchPda)`: Direct fetch by address\n- All return `UIMatch | null`, wrap in try-catch\n\n**Instruction Builders** — All return formatted Anchor instructions:\n- `buildCreateMatchInstruction()` / `buildCreateMatchTx()`\n- `buildJoinMatchTx()` — derives Orao VRF accounts\n- `buildCancelMatchTx()`\n- `buildTimeoutCancelTx()`\n- `buildClaimPayoutTx()` — fetches config for treasury, derives player profile PDAs\n\n---\n\n### **types.ts** — Type Definitions\n\n**UIMatch Interface (Lines 9-42)** — Frontend-facing match representation:\n```typescript\nexport interface UIMatch {\n  id: string;                          // matchPda.toBase58()\n  tier: Tier;                          // \"iron\" | \"bronze\" | \"silver\" | \"gold\" | \"platinum\" | \"diamond\"\n  entryAmount: number;                 // in $ (SOL equivalent)\n  \n  player1: string;                     // creator wallet address\n  player1Side: CoinSide;               // \"heads\" | \"tails\"\n  \n  player2: string | null;              // opponent wallet address or null\n  player2Side: CoinSide | null;        // opposite of player1, or null\n  \n  phase: CoinflipPhase;                // \"created\" | \"ready\" | \"countdown\" | \"flipping\" | \"complete\"\n  createdAt: number;                   // timestamp (ms)\n  lockedAt?: number;                   // when match entered LOCKED phase (ms)\n  countdownStartedAt?: number;         // when countdown started\n  completedAt?: number;                // when match settled\n  \n  result: CoinSide | null;             // winning side or null\n  winner: string | null;               // winner wallet address or null\n  \n  claimed: boolean;                    // payout claimed flag\n  payoutAmount: number;                // amount winner receives\n  \n  seedHash: string;                    // SHA-256 hash of server seed (pre-flip)\n  serverSeed?: string;                 // actual seed (post-settlement)\n  vrfProof?: string;                   // VRF proof for verification\n  blockHash?: string;                  // Solana blockhash entropy\n}\n```\n\n**Related Types (Lines 3-4, 44-56)**:\n- `CoinSide`: `\"heads\" | \"tails\"`\n- `CoinflipPhase`: `\"created\" | \"ready\" | \"countdown\" | \"flipping\" | \"complete\"`\n- `MatchFilter`: optional tier/status filters\n- `CreateMatchParams`: tier + side\n- `JoinMatchParams`: matchId\n\n---\n\n## Key Observations\n\n1. **No memcmp filtering**: Current code uses `program.account.coinflipMatch.all()` with in-memory filtering, not optimized Blockscout filter syntax\n2. **Phase conversion**: UI phases (`created`, `ready`, `complete`) map to on-chain phases (`waiting`, `locked`, `settled`)\n3. **Program ID flexible**: Loads from env, allows env override of IDL default\n4. **Payout hardcoded**: Always 97% (fixed 3% fee), no dynamic lookup\n5. **PDA structure**: Match PDA uses only `creator` as seed (one match per creator at a time)\n6. **Type safety gap**: Lots of `as unknown as OnChainMatch` casts (expected for Anchor deserialization)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a5cd6941ae59ac966 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 34478\ntool_uses: 2\nduration_ms: 19640</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ea1b77b2-5fe0-46a2-b598-5cd4b215a0f0","uuid":"320cc634-10a8-46d4-8ca0-79df5b685f15","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the full contents of `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts`. I need to understand:\n1. How existing fetch functions work (fetchAllOpenMatches, fe