{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YBNKsqtdA9gtKvTmSu872z","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→use anchor_lang::prelude::*;\n     2→\n     3→/// Lifecycle phase for every round/match in any game.\n     4→#[derive(AnchorSerialize, AnchorDeserialize, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Debug, InitSpace)]\n     5→pub enum RoundPhase {\n     6→    Waiting,\n     7→    Active,\n     8→    Locked,\n     9→    Resolving,\n    10→    Settled,\n    11→    Refunded,\n    12→}\n    13→\n    14→/// Timestamps tracking round progression.\n    15→#[derive(AnchorSerialize, AnchorDeserialize, Clone, Copy, Debug)]\n    16→pub struct RoundTimestamps {\n    17→    pub created_at: i64,\n    18→    pub locked_at: Option<i64>,\n    19→    pub resolve_deadline: Option<i64>,\n    20→    pub settled_at: Option<i64>,\n    21→}\n    22→\n    23→#[error_code]\n    24→pub enum LifecycleError {\n    25→    #[msg(\"Invalid phase transition\")]\n    26→    InvalidTransition,\n    27→}\n    28→\n    29→/// Validates that the transition from `current` to `target` is allowed.\n    30→///\n    31→/// Allowed transitions:\n    32→/// - Waiting → Active, Locked, Refunded\n    33→/// - Active → Locked, Refunded\n    34→/// - Locked → Resolving, Refunded\n    35→/// - Resolving → Settled, Refunded\n    36→///\n    37→/// LOCKED → SETTLED is explicitly disallowed; VRF games read the result\n    38→/// at claim time and set the phase directly.\n    39→pub fn transition(current: RoundPhase, target: RoundPhase) -> Result<()> {\n    40→    let valid = matches!(\n    41→        (current, target),\n    42→        (RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Active)\n    43→            | (RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Locked)\n    44→            | (RoundPhase::Active, RoundPhase::Locked)\n    45→            | (RoundPhase::Locked, RoundPhase::Resolving)\n    46→            | (RoundPhase::Resolving, RoundPhase::Settled)\n    47→            | (RoundPhase::Resolving, RoundPhase::Refunded)\n    48→            | (RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Refunded)\n    49→            | (RoundPhase::Active, RoundPhase::Refunded)\n    50→            | (RoundPhase::Locked, RoundPhase::Refunded)\n    51→    );\n    52→\n    53→    if valid {\n    54→        Ok(())\n    55→    } else {\n    56→        Err(LifecycleError::InvalidTransition.into())\n    57→    }\n    58→}\n    59→\n    60→#[cfg(test)]\n    61→mod tests {\n    62→    use super::*;\n    63→\n    64→    #[test]\n    65→    fn valid_transitions() {\n    66→        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Active).is_ok());\n    67→        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Locked).is_ok());\n    68→        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Active, RoundPhase::Locked).is_ok());\n    69→        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Locked, RoundPhase::Resolving).is_ok());\n    70→        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Resolving, RoundPhase::Settled).is_ok());\n    71→        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Resolving, RoundPhase::Refunded).is_ok());\n    72→        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Refunded).is_ok());\n    73→        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Active, RoundPhase::Refunded).is_ok());\n    74→        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Locked, RoundPhase::Refunded).is_ok());\n    75→    }\n    76→\n    77→    #[test]\n    78→    fn invalid_transitions() {\n    79→        // Self-transitions\n    80→        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Waiting).is_err());\n    81→        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Locked, RoundPhase::Locked).is_err());\n    82→\n    83→        // Backward transitions\n    84→        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Active, RoundPhase::Waiting).is_err());\n    85→        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Locked, RoundPhase::Waiting).is_err());\n    86→        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Settled, RoundPhase::Waiting).is_err());\n    87→\n    88→        // LOCKED → SETTLED explicitly invalid (VRF games use claim, not transition)\n    89→        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Locked, RoundPhase::Settled).is_err());\n    90→\n    91→        // Terminal states cannot transition\n    92→        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Settled, RoundPhase::Refunded).is_err());\n    93→        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Refunded, RoundPhase::Settled).is_err());\n    94→\n    95→        // Skip transitions\n    96→        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Settled).is_err());\n    97→        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Resolving).is_err());\n    98→    }\n    99→\n   100→    #[test]\n   101→    fn enum_serialization_roundtrip() {\n   102→        let phases = [\n   103→            RoundPhase::Waiting,\n   104→            RoundPhase::Active,\n   105→            RoundPhase::Locked,\n   106→            RoundPhase::Resolving,\n   107→            RoundPhase::Settled,\n   108→            RoundPhase::Refunded,\n   109→        ];\n   110→\n   111→        for phase in phases {\n   112→            let mut buf = Vec::new();\n   113→            AnchorSerialize::serialize(&phase, &mut buf).unwrap();\n   114→            let deserialized = RoundPhase::deserialize(&mut buf.as_slice()).unwrap();\n   115→            assert_eq!(phase, deserialized);\n   116→        }\n   117→    }\n   118→}\n   119→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_019LiVqen3fjEKMFS3J7yW94","session_id":"ea1b77b2-5fe0-46a2-b598-5cd4b215a0f0","uuid":"0403014b-8bad-4146-800f-7a8613c114a5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019LiVqen3fjEKMFS3J7yW94","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile the comprehensive report:\n\n## CoinflipMatch On-Chain State Layout - Memcmp Filter Offset Calculations\n\n### Field Order and Byte Offsets\n\nBased on the `CoinflipMatch` struct in `state.rs` and the IDL definition, here is the exact field layout with byte offsets:\n\n```\nOffset    Field              Type         Size (bytes)    Notes\n─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n0-7       [Discriminator]    u64          8               Anchor auto-prepends this\n8-39      creator            Pubkey       32              First field after discriminator\n40-71     opponent           Pubkey       32              Default if not joined\n72        tier               u8           1               0-5\n73-80     entry_amount       u64          8               Lamports\n81        creator_side       u8           1               0 = Heads, 1 = Tails\n82        phase              RoundPhase    1               Enum (0-5)\n83        result             u8           1               0 or 1\n84-115    winner             Pubkey       32              Default until settled\n116       claimed            bool         1               0 or 1\n117-124   created_at         i64          8               Unix timestamp\n125-132   locked_at          i64          8               Unix timestamp (0 if WAITING)\n133-140   resolve_deadline   i64          8               Unix timestamp\n141-172   vrf_request_key    Pubkey       32              Orao randomness PDA\n173       bump               u8           1               PDA bump seed\n─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nTOTAL ACCOUNT SIZE: 174 bytes (8 discriminator + 166 struct data)\n```\n\n### Key Field Offsets for memcmp Filters\n\n| Field | Offset (in bytes) | Size (bytes) | Type | Usage |\n|-------|------------------|-------------|------|-------|\n| **creator** | 8 | 32 | Pubkey | Filter: `memcmp offset 8 bytes [pubkey_bytes]` |\n| **opponent** | 40 | 32 | Pubkey | Filter: `memcmp offset 40 bytes [pubkey_bytes]` |\n| **phase** | 82 | 1 | RoundPhase enum | Filter: `memcmp offset 82 bytes [phase_value]` |\n| **claimed** | 116 | 1 | bool | Filter: `memcmp offset 116 bytes [0x00 or 0x01]` |\n| **winner** | 84 | 32 | Pubkey | Filter: `memcmp offset 84 bytes [pubkey_bytes]` |\n| **result** | 83 | 1 | u8 | Filter: `memcmp offset 83 bytes [0 or 1]` |\n\n### Anchor Discriminator\n\n- **Size**: 8 bytes\n- **Value for CoinflipMatch**: `[99, 15, 226, 250, 130, 64, 231, 38]` (from IDL)\n- **Usage**: Always prepended as first 8 bytes; account deserialization automatically strips this\n\n### Phase Constants and Values\n\nThe `RoundPhase` enum is defined in `solana/shared/src/lifecycle.rs`. As an Anchor enum, each variant is serialized as a single byte in order:\n\n| Variant | Value | Notes |\n|---------|-------|-------|\n| `Waiting` | 0 | Creator placed bet, waiting for opponent |\n| `Active` | 1 | Both players in (used for non-VRF games) |\n| `Locked` | 2 | Both players in, requesting VRF |\n| `Resolving` | 3 | VRF request in flight |\n| `Settled` | 4 | VRF resolved, winner determined |\n| `Refunded` | 5 | Match cancelled/timed out |\n\n**Important**: The older constants in `solana/shared/src/constants.rs` (PHASE_WAITING = 0, PHASE_LOCKED = 1, PHASE_SETTLED = 2, PHASE_CANCELLED = 3) are **deprecated** for coinflip. Use the `RoundPhase` enum values instead.\n\n### Side Constants (for creator_side and result fields)\n\n| Constant | Value | Meaning |\n|----------|-------|---------|\n| `SIDE_HEADS` | 0 | Heads |\n| `SIDE_TAILS` | 1 | Tails |\n\n---\n\n### Example memcmp Filters\n\nTo query for a specific creator's match in LOCKED phase with not yet claimed:\n\n```javascript\n// Find matches by creator (offset 8, 32 bytes for pubkey)\n{\n  memcmp: {\n    offset: 8,\n    bytes: creatorPublicKey.toBase58() // Anchor base58-encodes pubkeys in memcmp\n  }\n}\n\n// AND phase = LOCKED (offset 82, 1 byte value=2)\n{\n  memcmp: {\n    offset: 82,\n    bytes: bs58.encode(Buffer.from([2]))\n  }\n}\n\n// AND claimed = false (offset 116, 1 byte value=0)\n{\n  memcmp: {\n    offset: 116,\n    bytes: bs58.encode(Buffer.from([0]))\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### File References\n\n- **State definition**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs` (lines 19-52)\n- **Phase enum**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/lifecycle.rs` (lines 5-12)\n- **Old phase constants** (deprecated): `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/constants.rs` (lines 5-8)\n- **IDL definition**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/coinflip.json` (lines 743-854)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: adac3f3d6cbef0cce (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 43791\ntool_uses: 12\nduration_ms: 40268</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ea1b77b2-5fe0-46a2-b598-5cd4b215a0f0","uuid":"e46ac847-fb94-40ef-ac07-4f40356def94","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the CoinflipMatch on-chain state layout to calculate byte offsets for memcmp filters. Find and read:\n1. `solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs` - the match state struct\n2. `solana/shared/src/constants.rs` - phase constants and side constants\n3. The Anchor IDL for coinflip at `sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/coinflip.json` - specifically the CoinflipMatch account type definition to understand field ordering and sizes\n\nFor the IDL, I specifically need the accounts section that defines CoinflipMatch fields, their types and order. This is critical for calculating memcmp offsets.\n\nReport back:\n- The exact field order of CoinflipMatch\n- The byte size of each field\n- The discriminator size (8 bytes for Anchor)\n