{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Dpu8dZzhyE4okiummAsHnP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import { Program, AnchorProvider, type Idl } from \"@coral-xyz/anchor\";\n     2→import {\n     3→  Connection,\n     4→  PublicKey,\n     5→  SystemProgram,\n     6→  Transaction,\n     7→  type TransactionInstruction,\n     8→} from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n     9→import { CoinflipIDL, type Coinflip } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\n    10→import {\n    11→  TIER_VALUES,\n    12→  COIN_SIDE_VALUES,\n    13→  TIER_AMOUNTS,\n    14→  type Tier,\n    15→  type CoinSide,\n    16→} from \"@rng-utopia/game-engine/browser\";\n    17→import type { UIMatch } from \"../types\";\n    18→\n    19→// ============ Constants ============\n    20→\n    21→const COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n    22→  (import.meta as unknown as { env: Record<string, string | undefined> }).env\n    23→    .VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID ?? CoinflipIDL.address\n    24→);\n    25→\n    26→// Orao VRF program (on-chain VRF provider)\n    27→const ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\"VRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y\");\n    28→\n    29→// ============ PDA Derivation ============\n    30→\n    31→export function getMatchPda(creator: PublicKey): [PublicKey, number] {\n    32→  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    33→    [Buffer.from(\"match\"), creator.toBuffer()],\n    34→    COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID\n    35→  );\n    36→}\n    37→\n    38→export function getConfigPda(): [PublicKey, number] {\n    39→  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    40→    [Buffer.from(\"coinflip_config\")],\n    41→    COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID\n    42→  );\n    43→}\n    44→\n    45→/** Orao VRF network state PDA (stores config + treasury). */\n    46→function getOraoNetworkStatePda(): PublicKey {\n    47→  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    48→    [Buffer.from(\"orao-vrf-network-configuration\")],\n    49→    ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID\n    50→  );\n    51→  return pda;\n    52→}\n    53→\n    54→/** Orao VRF randomness PDA derived from a 32-byte seed. */\n    55→function getOraoRandomnessPda(seed: Uint8Array): PublicKey {\n    56→  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    57→    [Buffer.from(\"orao-vrf-randomness-request\"), seed],\n    58→    ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID\n    59→  );\n    60→  return pda;\n    61→}\n    62→\n    63→// ============ Program Instance ============\n    64→\n    65→function getCoinflipProgram(connection: Connection): Program<Coinflip> {\n    66→  // Read-only provider (no wallet needed for queries)\n    67→  const provider = new AnchorProvider(\n    68→    connection,\n    69→    {} as AnchorProvider[\"wallet\"],\n    70→    { commitment: \"confirmed\" }\n    71→  );\n    72→  return new Program(CoinflipIDL as Idl as Coinflip, provider);\n    73→}\n    74→\n    75→// ============ On-Chain Account Types ============\n    76→\n    77→/** Anchor enum variant representation — one key with empty object value. */\n    78→type RoundPhaseVariant = { waiting: object } | { active: object } | { locked: object }\n    79→  | { resolving: object } | { settled: object } | { refunded: object };\n    80→\n    81→interface OnChainMatch {\n    82→  creator: PublicKey;\n    83→  opponent: PublicKey;\n    84→  tier: number;\n    85→  entryAmount: { toNumber(): number };\n    86→  creatorSide: number;\n    87→  phase: RoundPhaseVariant;\n    88→  result: number;\n    89→  winner: PublicKey;\n    90→  claimed: boolean;\n    91→  createdAt: { toNumber(): number };\n    92→  lockedAt: { toNumber(): number };\n    93→  resolveDeadline: { toNumber(): number };\n    94→  vrfRequestKey: PublicKey;\n    95→  bump: number;\n    96→}\n    97→\n    98→// ============ Converters ============\n    99→\n   100→function tierFromIndex(index: number): Tier {\n   101→  const tiers: Tier[] = [\"iron\", \"bronze\", \"silver\", \"gold\", \"platinum\", \"diamond\"];\n   102→  return tiers[index] ?? \"iron\";\n   103→}\n   104→\n   105→function sideFromIndex(index: number): CoinSide {\n   106→  return index === 0 ? \"heads\" : \"tails\";\n   107→}\n   108→\n   109→function isPhase(phase: RoundPhaseVariant, name: string): boolean {\n   110→  return name in phase;\n   111→}\n   112→\n   113→function phaseToUI(phase: RoundPhaseVariant): UIMatch[\"phase\"] {\n   114→  if (isPhase(phase, \"waiting\")) return \"created\";\n   115→  if (isPhase(phase, \"locked\")) return \"ready\";\n   116→  if (isPhase(phase, \"settled\")) return \"complete\";\n   117→  return \"created\";\n   118→}\n   119→\n   120→const DEFAULT_PUBKEY = PublicKey.default;\n   121→\n   122→function isDefaultPubkey(key: PublicKey): boolean {\n   123→  return key.equals(DEFAULT_PUBKEY);\n   124→}\n   125→\n   126→export function onChainMatchToUI(\n   127→  matchPda: PublicKey,\n   128→  data: OnChainMatch\n   129→): UIMatch {\n   130→  const tier = tierFromIndex(data.tier);\n   131→  const creatorSide = sideFromIndex(data.creatorSide);\n   132→  const hasOpponent = !isDefaultPubkey(data.opponent);\n   133→  const phase = phaseToUI(data.phase);\n   134→  const isSettled = isPhase(data.phase, \"settled\");\n   135→\n   136→  const entryAmountSol = TIER_AMOUNTS[tier];\n   137→  const totalPool = entryAmountSol * 2;\n   138→  const payoutAmount = totalPool * 0.97;\n   139→\n   140→  const lockedAt = data.lockedAt.toNumber();\n   141→\n   142→  return {\n   143→    id: matchPda.toBase58(),\n   144→    tier,\n   145→    entryAmount: entryAmountSol,\n   146→    player1: data.creator.toBase58(),\n   147→    player1Side: creatorSide,\n   148→    player2: hasOpponent ? data.opponent.toBase58() : null,\n   149→    player2Side: hasOpponent\n   150→      ? (creatorSide === \"heads\" ? \"tails\" : \"heads\")\n   151→      : null,\n   152→    phase,\n   153→    createdAt: Date.now(),\n   154→    lockedAt: lockedAt > 0 ? lockedAt * 1000 : undefined,\n   155→    result: isSettled ? sideFromIndex(data.result) : null,\n   156→    winner: isSettled && !isDefaultPubkey(data.winner)\n   157→      ? data.winner.toBase58()\n   158→      : null,\n   159→    claimed: data.claimed,\n   160→    payoutAmount,\n   161→    seedHash: \"\",\n   162→  };\n   163→}\n   164→\n   165→// ============ Account Queries ============\n   166→\n   167→export async function fetchAllOpenMatches(\n   168→  connection: Connection\n   169→): Promise<UIMatch[]> {\n   170→  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n   171→  const accounts = await program.account.coinflipMatch.all();\n   172→\n   173→  return accounts\n   174→    .filter((acc) => isPhase((acc.account as unknown as OnChainMatch).phase, \"waiting\"))\n   175→    .map((acc) =>\n   176→      onChainMatchToUI(\n   177→        acc.publicKey,\n   178→        acc.account as unknown as OnChainMatch\n   179→      )\n   180→    );\n   181→}\n   182→\n   183→export async function fetchMatchByCreator(\n   184→  connection: Connection,\n   185→  creator: PublicKey\n   186→): Promise<UIMatch | null> {\n   187→  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n   188→  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(creator);\n   189→\n   190→  try {\n   191→    const account = await program.account.coinflipMatch.fetch(matchPda);\n   192→    return onChainMatchToUI(matchPda, account as unknown as OnChainMatch);\n   193→  } catch {\n   194→    // Account doesn't exist\n   195→    return null;\n   196→  }\n   197→}\n   198→\n   199→export async function fetchMatch(\n   200→  connection: Connection,\n   201→  matchPda: PublicKey\n   202→): Promise<UIMatch | null> {\n   203→  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n   204→\n   205→  try {\n   206→    const account = await program.account.coinflipMatch.fetch(matchPda);\n   207→    return onChainMatchToUI(matchPda, account as unknown as OnChainMatch);\n   208→  } catch {\n   209→    return null;\n   210→  }\n   211→}\n   212→\n   213→// ============ Instruction Builders ============\n   214→\n   215→export function buildCreateMatchInstruction(\n   216→  creator: PublicKey,\n   217→  tier: Tier,\n   218→  side: CoinSide\n   219→): { instruction: TransactionInstruction; matchPda: PublicKey } {\n   220→  const program = getCoinflipProgram(new Connection(\"http://127.0.0.1:8899\"));\n   221→  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(creator);\n   222→  const [configPda] = getConfigPda();\n   223→\n   224→  const tierIndex = TIER_VALUES[tier];\n   225→  const sideIndex = COIN_SIDE_VALUES[side];\n   226→\n   227→  const instruction = program.methods\n   228→    .createMatch(tierIndex, sideIndex)\n   229→    .accountsStrict({\n   230→      creator,\n   231→      coinflipMatch: matchPda,\n   232→      config: configPda,\n   233→      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n   234→    })\n   235→    .instruction();\n   236→\n   237→  // instruction() returns a Promise<TransactionInstruction>, but we return\n   238→  // it synchronously wrapped — callers must await the instruction.\n   239→  return { instruction: instruction as unknown as TransactionInstruction, matchPda };\n   240→}\n   241→\n   242→export async function buildCreateMatchTx(\n   243→  connection: Connection,\n   244→  creator: PublicKey,\n   245→  tier: Tier,\n   246→  side: CoinSide\n   247→): Promise<{ transaction: Transaction; matchPda: PublicKey }> {\n   248→  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n   249→  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(creator);\n   250→  const [configPda] = getConfigPda();\n   251→\n   252→  const tierIndex = TIER_VALUES[tier];\n   253→  const sideIndex = COIN_SIDE_VALUES[side];\n   254→\n   255→  const ix = await program.methods\n   256→    .createMatch(tierIndex, sideIndex)\n   257→    .accountsStrict({\n   258→      creator,\n   259→      coinflipMatch: matchPda,\n   260→      config: configPda,\n   261→      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n   262→    })\n   263→    .instruction();\n   264→\n   265→  const tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\n   266→  tx.feePayer = creator;\n   267→  tx.recentBlockhash = (await connection.getLatestBlockhash()).blockhash;\n   268→\n   269→  return { transaction: tx, matchPda };\n   270→}\n   271→\n   272→export async function buildJoinMatchTx(\n   273→  connection: Connection,\n   274→  opponent: PublicKey,\n   275→  matchCreator: PublicKey\n   276→): Promise<Transaction> {\n   277→  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n   278→  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(matchCreator);\n   279→  const [configPda] = getConfigPda();\n   280→\n   281→  // Orao VRF accounts — derive PDAs and fetch treasury from network state\n   282→  const oraoNetworkState = getOraoNetworkStatePda();\n   283→  const networkInfo = await connection.getAccountInfo(oraoNetworkState);\n   284→  if (!networkInfo) throw new Error(\"Orao VRF network state not found on-chain\");\n   285→  // Treasury is at offset 40 in Orao NetworkState (8-byte discriminator + 32-byte authority)\n   286→  const oraoTreasury = new PublicKey(networkInfo.data.subarray(40, 72));\n   287→  const oraoRandom = getOraoRandomnessPda(matchPda.toBytes());\n   288→\n   289→  const ix = await program.methods\n   290→    .joinMatch()\n   291→    .accountsStrict({\n   292→      opponent,\n   293→      coinflipMatch: matchPda,\n   294→      config: configPda,\n   295→      oraoProgram: ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID,\n   296→      oraoNetworkState,\n   297→      oraoTreasury,\n   298→      oraoRandom,\n   299→      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n   300→    })\n   301→    .instruction();\n   302→\n   303→  const tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\n   304→  tx.feePayer = opponent;\n   305→  tx.recentBlockhash = (await connection.getLatestBlockhash()).blockhash;\n   306→\n   307→  return tx;\n   308→}\n   309→\n   310→export async function buildCancelMatchTx(\n   311→  connection: Connection,\n   312→  creator: PublicKey\n   313→): Promise<Transaction> {\n   314→  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n   315→  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(creator);\n   316→\n   317→  const ix = await program.methods\n   318→    .cancelMatch()\n   319→    .accountsStrict({\n   320→      creator,\n   321→      coinflipMatch: matchPda,\n   322→      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n   323→    })\n   324→    .instruction();\n   325→\n   326→  const tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\n   327→  tx.feePayer = creator;\n   328→  tx.recentBlockhash = (await connection.getLatestBlockhash()).blockhash;\n   329→\n   330→  return tx;\n   331→}\n   332→\n   333→export async function buildTimeoutCancelTx(\n   334→  connection: Connection,\n   335→  caller: PublicKey,\n   336→  matchCreator: PublicKey,\n   337→  opponent: PublicKey\n   338→): Promise<Transaction> {\n   339→  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n   340→  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(matchCreator);\n   341→\n   342→  // Derive randomness account from match PDA (VRF seed = match PDA key)\n   343→  const randomnessAccount = getOraoRandomnessPda(matchPda.toBytes());\n   344→\n   345→  const ix = await program.methods\n   346→    .timeoutCancel()\n   347→    .accountsStrict({\n   348→      caller,\n   349→      creator: matchCreator,\n   350→      opponent,\n   351→      coinflipMatch: matchPda,\n   352→      randomnessAccount,\n   353→    })\n   354→    .instruction();\n   355→\n   356→  const tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\n   357→  tx.feePayer = caller;\n   358→  tx.recentBlockhash = (await connection.getLatestBlockhash()).blockhash;\n   359→\n   360→  return tx;\n   361→}\n   362→\n   363→export async function buildClaimPayoutTx(\n   364→  connection: Connection,\n   365→  caller: PublicKey,\n   366→  matchCreator: PublicKey,\n   367→  opponent: PublicKey\n   368→): Promise<Transaction> {\n   369→  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n   370→  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(matchCreator);\n   371→  const [configPda] = getConfigPda();\n   372→\n   373→  // Fetch config to get treasury address\n   374→  const config = await program.account.coinflipConfig.fetch(configPda);\n   375→  const treasury = (config as unknown as { treasury: PublicKey }).treasury;\n   376→\n   377→  // Derive randomness account from match PDA (VRF seed = match PDA key)\n   378→  const randomnessAccount = getOraoRandomnessPda(matchPda.toBytes());\n   379→\n   380→  // Derive player profile PDAs for CPI\n   381→  const PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n   382→    (import.meta as unknown as { env: Record<string, string | undefined> }).env\n   383→      .VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID ?? \"dYJcBccf1M7yDePcgmiytiEtwr7n4fAaLQAhVPNHgVM\"\n   384→  );\n   385→  const [creatorProfile] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n   386→    [Buffer.from(\"player_profile\"), matchCreator.toBuffer()],\n   387→    PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID\n   388→  );\n   389→  const [opponentProfile] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n   390→    [Buffer.from(\"player_profile\"), opponent.toBuffer()],\n   391→    PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID\n   392→  );\n   393→\n   394→  const ix = await program.methods\n   395→    .claimPayout()\n   396→    .accountsStrict({\n   397→      caller,\n   398→      coinflipMatch: matchPda,\n   399→      config: configPda,\n   400→      treasury,\n   401→      creator: matchCreator,\n   402→      opponent,\n   403→      randomnessAccount,\n   404→      creatorProfile,\n   405→      opponentProfile,\n   406→      platformProgram: PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID,\n   407→      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n   408→    })\n   409→    .instruction();\n   410→\n   411→  const tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\n   412→  tx.feePayer = caller;\n   413→  tx.recentBlockhash = (await connection.getLatestBlockhash()).blockhash;\n   414→\n   415→  return tx;\n   416→}\n   417→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ea1b77b2-5fe0-46a2-b598-5cd4b215a0f0","uuid":"cf5f2e2a-1f10-405b-96be-f9a682044258","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts","content":"import { Program, AnchorProvider, type Idl } from \"@coral-xyz/anchor\";\nimport {\n  Connection,\n  PublicKey,\n  SystemProgram,\n  Transaction,\n  type TransactionInstruction,\n} from \"@solana/web3.js\";\nimport { CoinflipIDL, type Coinflip } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\nimport {\n  TIER_VALUES,\n  COIN_SIDE_VALUES,\n  TIER_AMOUNTS,\n  type Tier,\n  type CoinSide,\n} from \"@rng-utopia/game-engine/browser\";\nimport type { UIMatch } from \"../types\";\n\n// ============ Constants ============\n\nconst COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n  (import.meta as unknown as { env: Record<string, string | undefined> }).env\n    .VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID ?? CoinflipIDL.address\n);\n\n// Orao VRF program (on-chain VRF provider)\nconst ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\"VRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y\");\n\n// ============ PDA Derivation ============\n\nexport function getMatchPda(creator: PublicKey): [PublicKey, number] {\n  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"match\"), creator.toBuffer()],\n    COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n}\n\nexport function getConfigPda(): [PublicKey, number] {\n  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"coinflip_config\")],\n    COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n}\n\n/** Orao VRF network state PDA (stores config + treasury). */\nfunction getOraoNetworkStatePda(): PublicKey {\n  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"orao-vrf-network-configuration\")],\n    ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n  return pda;\n}\n\n/** Orao VRF randomness PDA derived from a 32-byte seed. */\nfunction getOraoRandomnessPda(seed: Uint8Array): PublicKey {\n  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"orao-vrf-randomness-request\"), seed],\n    ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n  return pda;\n}\n\n// ============ Program Instance ============\n\nfunction getCoinflipProgram(connection: Connection): Program<Coinflip> {\n  // Read-only provider (no wallet needed for queries)\n  const provider = new AnchorProvider(\n    connection,\n    {} as AnchorProvider[\"wallet\"],\n    { commitment: \"confirmed\" }\n  );\n  return new Program(CoinflipIDL as Idl as Coinflip, provider);\n}\n\n// ============ On-Chain Account Types ============\n\n/** Anchor enum variant representation — one key with empty object value. */\ntype RoundPhaseVariant = { waiting: object } | { active: object } | { locked: object }\n  | { resolving: object } | { settled: object } | { refunded: object };\n\ninterface OnChainMatch {\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  opponent: PublicKey;\n  tier: number;\n  entryAmount: { toNumber(): number };\n  creatorSide: number;\n  phase: RoundPhaseVariant;\n  result: number;\n  winner: PublicKey;\n  claimed: boolean;\n  createdAt: { toNumber(): number };\n  lockedAt: { toNumber(): number };\n  resolveDeadline: { toNumber(): number };\n  vrfRequestKey: PublicKey;\n  bump: number;\n}\n\n// ============ Converters ============\n\nfunction tierFromIndex(index: number): Tier {\n  const tiers: Tier[] = [\"iron\", \"bronze\", \"silver\", \"gold\", \"platinum\", \"diamond\"];\n  return tiers[index] ?? \"iron\";\n}\n\nfunction sideFromIndex(index: number): CoinSide {\n  return index === 0 ? \"heads\" : \"tails\";\n}\n\nfunction isPhase(phase: RoundPhaseVariant, name: string): boolean {\n  return name in phase;\n}\n\nfunction phaseToUI(phase: RoundPhaseVariant): UIMatch[\"phase\"] {\n  if (isPhase(phase, \"waiting\")) return \"created\";\n  if (isPhase(phase, \"locked\")) return \"ready\";\n  if (isPhase(phase, \"settled\")) return \"complete\";\n  return \"created\";\n}\n\nconst DEFAULT_PUBKEY = PublicKey.default;\n\nfunction isDefaultPubkey(key: PublicKey): boolean {\n  return key.equals(DEFAULT_PUBKEY);\n}\n\nexport function onChainMatchToUI(\n  matchPda: PublicKey,\n  data: OnChainMatch\n): UIMatch {\n  const tier = tierFromIndex(data.tier);\n  const creatorSide = sideFromIndex(data.creatorSide);\n  const hasOpponent = !isDefaultPubkey(data.opponent);\n  const phase = phaseToUI(data.phase);\n  const isSettled = isPhase(data.phase, \"settled\");\n\n  const entryAmountSol = TIER_AMOUNTS[tier];\n  const totalPool = entryAmountSol * 2;\n  const payoutAmount = totalPool * 0.97;\n\n  const lockedAt = data.lockedAt.toNumber();\n\n  return {\n    id: matchPda.toBase58(),\n    tier,\n    entryAmount: entryAmountSol,\n    player1: data.creator.toBase58(),\n    player1Side: creatorSide,\n    player2: hasOpponent ? data.opponent.toBase58() : null,\n    player2Side: hasOpponent\n      ? (creatorSide === \"heads\" ? \"tails\" : \"heads\")\n      : null,\n    phase,\n    createdAt: Date.now(),\n    lockedAt: lockedAt > 0 ? lockedAt * 1000 : undefined,\n    result: isSettled ? sideFromIndex(data.result) : null,\n    winner: isSettled && !isDefaultPubkey(data.winner)\n      ? data.winner.toBase58()\n      : null,\n    claimed: data.claimed,\n    payoutAmount,\n    seedHash: \"\",\n  };\n}\n\n// ============ Account Queries ============\n\nexport async function fetchAllOpenMatches(\n  connection: Connection\n): Promise<UIMatch[]> {\n  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n  const accounts = await program.account.coinflipMatch.all();\n\n  return accounts\n    .filter((acc) => isPhase((acc.account as unknown as OnChainMatch).phase, \"waiting\"))\n    .map((acc) =>\n      onChainMatchToUI(\n        acc.publicKey,\n        acc.account as unknown as OnChainMatch\n      )\n    );\n}\n\nexport async function fetchMatchByCreator(\n  connection: Connection,\n  creator: PublicKey\n): Promise<UIMatch | null> {\n  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(creator);\n\n  try {\n    const account = await program.account.coinflipMatch.fetch(matchPda);\n    return onChainMatchToUI(matchPda, account as unknown as OnChainMatch);\n  } catch {\n    // Account doesn't exist\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\nexport async function fetchMatch(\n  connection: Connection,\n  matchPda: PublicKey\n): Promise<UIMatch | null> {\n  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n\n  try {\n    const account = await program.account.coinflipMatch.fetch(matchPda);\n    return onChainMatchToUI(matchPda, account as unknown as OnChainMatch);\n  } catch {\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\n// ============ Instruction Builders ============\n\nexport function buildCreateMatchInstruction(\n  creator: PublicKey,\n  tier: Tier,\n  side: CoinSide\n): { instruction: TransactionInstruction; matchPda: PublicKey } {\n  const program = getCoinflipProgram(new Connection(\"http://127.0.0.1:8899\"));\n  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(creator);\n  const [configPda] = getConfigPda();\n\n  const tierIndex = TIER_VALUES[tier];\n  const sideIndex = COIN_SIDE_VALUES[side];\n\n  const instruction = program.methods\n    .createMatch(tierIndex, sideIndex)\n    .accountsStrict({\n      creator,\n      coinflipMatch: matchPda,\n      config: configPda,\n      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n    })\n    .instruction();\n\n  // instruction() returns a Promise<TransactionInstruction>, but we return\n  // it synchronously wrapped — callers must await the instruction.\n  return { instruction: instruction as unknown as TransactionInstruction, matchPda };\n}\n\nexport async function buildCreateMatchTx(\n  connection: Connection,\n  creator: PublicKey,\n  tier: Tier,\n  side: CoinSide\n): Promise<{ transaction: Transaction; matchPda: PublicKey }> {\n  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(creator);\n  const [configPda] = getConfigPda();\n\n  const tierIndex = TIER_VALUES[tier];\n  const sideIndex = COIN_SIDE_VALUES[side];\n\n  const ix = await program.methods\n    .createMatch(tierIndex, sideIndex)\n    .accountsStrict({\n      creator,\n      coinflipMatch: matchPda,\n      config: configPda,\n      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n    })\n    .instruction();\n\n  const tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\n  tx.feePayer = creator;\n  tx.recentBlockhash = (await connection.getLatestBlockhash()).blockhash;\n\n  return { transaction: tx, matchPda };\n}\n\nexport async function buildJoinMatchTx(\n  connection: Connection,\n  opponent: PublicKey,\n  matchCreator: PublicKey\n): Promise<Transaction> {\n  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(matchCreator);\n  const [configPda] = getConfigPda();\n\n  // Orao VRF accounts — derive PDAs and fetch treasury from network state\n  const oraoNetworkState = getOraoNetworkStatePda();\n  const networkInfo = await connection.getAccountInfo(oraoNetworkState);\n  if (!networkInfo) throw new Error(\"Orao VRF network state not found on-chain\");\n  // Treasury is at offset 40 in Orao NetworkState (8-byte discriminator + 32-byte authority)\n  const oraoTreasury = new PublicKey(networkInfo.data.subarray(40, 72));\n  const oraoRandom = getOraoRandomnessPda(matchPda.toBytes());\n\n  const ix = await program.methods\n    .joinMatch()\n    .accountsStrict({\n      opponent,\n      coinflipMatch: matchPda,\n      config: configPda,\n      oraoProgram: ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID,\n      oraoNetworkState,\n      oraoTreasury,\n      oraoRandom,\n      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n    })\n    .instruction();\n\n  const tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\n  tx.feePayer = opponent;\n  tx.recentBlockhash = (await connection.getLatestBlockhash()).blockhash;\n\n  return tx;\n}\n\nexport async function buildCancelMatchTx(\n  connection: Connection,\n  creator: PublicKey\n): Promise<Transaction> {\n  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(creator);\n\n  const ix = await program.methods\n    .cancelMatch()\n    .accountsStrict({\n      creator,\n      coinflipMatch: matchPda,\n      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n    })\n    .instruction();\n\n  const tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\n  tx.feePayer = creator;\n  tx.recentBlockhash = (await connection.getLatestBlockhash()).blockhash;\n\n  return tx;\n}\n\nexport async function buildTimeoutCancelTx(\n  connection: Connection,\n  caller: PublicKey,\n  matchCreator: PublicKey,\n  opponent: PublicKey\n): Promise<Transaction> {\n  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(matchCreator);\n\n  // Derive randomness account from match PDA (VRF seed = match PDA key)\n  const randomnessAccount = getOraoRandomnessPda(matchPda.toBytes());\n\n  const ix = await program.methods\n    .timeoutCancel()\n    .accountsStrict({\n      caller,\n      creator: matchCreator,\n      opponent,\n      coinflipMatch: matchPda,\n      randomnessAccount,\n    })\n    .instruction();\n\n  const tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\n  tx.feePayer = caller;\n  tx.recentBlockhash = (await connection.getLatestBlockhash()).blockhash;\n\n  return tx;\n}\n\nexport async function buildClaimPayoutTx(\n  connection: Connection,\n  caller: PublicKey,\n  matchCreator: PublicKey,\n  opponent: PublicKey\n): Promise<Transaction> {\n  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(matchCreator);\n  const [configPda] = getConfigPda();\n\n  // Fetch config to get treasury address\n  const config = await program.account.coinflipConfig.fetch(configPda);\n  const treasury = (config as unknown as { treasury: PublicKey }).treasury;\n\n  // Derive randomness account from match PDA (VRF seed = match PDA key)\n  const randomnessAccount = getOraoRandomnessPda(matchPda.toBytes());\n\n  // Derive player profile PDAs for CPI\n  const PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n    (import.meta as unknown as { env: Record<string, string | undefined> }).env\n      .VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID ?? \"dYJcBccf1M7yDePcgmiytiEtwr7n4fAaLQAhVPNHgVM\"\n  );\n  const [creatorProfile] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"player_profile\"), matchCreator.toBuffer()],\n    PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n  const [opponentProfile] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"player_profile\"), opponent.toBuffer()],\n    PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n\n  const ix = await program.methods\n    .claimPayout()\n    .accountsStrict({\n      caller,\n      coinflipMatch: matchPda,\n      config: configPda,\n      treasury,\n      creator: matchCreator,\n      opponent,\n      randomnessAccount,\n      creatorProfile,\n      opponentProfile,\n      platformProgram: PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID,\n      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n    })\n    .instruction();\n\n  const tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\n  tx.feePayer = caller;\n  tx.recentBlockhash = (await connection.getLatestBlockhash()).blockhash;\n\n  return tx;\n}\n","numLines":417,"startLine":1,"totalLines":417}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Qo3kQHgn5QmmTpGm6oQV8F","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need. Let me implement `fetchClaimableMatches`. The approach:\n\n1. Two `getProgramAccounts` queries with memcmp filters:\n   - Query 1: creator == playerPubkey AND claimed == false\n   - Query 2: opponent == playerPubkey AND claimed == false\n2. Post-filter to exclude `refunded` phase (terminal state)\n3. Deduplicate (in case player is both? Not possible, but safe)\n4. Convert to UIMatch[]\n\nKey offsets from the exploration:\n- Discriminator: 0-7 (8 bytes)\n\n\n- creator: offset 8 (32 bytes)\n- opponent: offset 40 (32 bytes)\n- tier: offset 72 (1 byte)\n- entry_amount: offset 73 (8 bytes)\n- creator_side: offset 81 (1 byte)\n- phase: offset 82 (1 byte)\n- result: offset 83 (1 byte)\n- winner: offset 84 (32 bytes)\n- claimed: offset 116 (1 byte)\n\nNow I'm setting up the memcmp filters using Anchor's `all()` method to query for matches where the player is either creator or opponent with claimed set to false. I need to verify the base58 encoding for a zero byte—it should encode to \"1\" since leading zeros map to that character in base58.\n\nNow I'm working on the actual implementation, setting up a function that queries for claimable matches by filtering accounts where the player is either the creator or opponent, using the Anchor program's `all()` method with memcmp filters to match the player's public key at the appropriate offsets.\n\nWriting the query function... Writing the match filtering logic...\n\nNow I'm verifying the byte offsets in the on-chain state struct to make sure the `claimed` field is at the right position—counting through the discriminator, public keys, and various u8 and u64 fields to confirm it lands at offset 116. So `bytes: \"1\"` correctly represents a single zero byte in base58 encoding, which matches the `claimed == false` state. The Solana JSON RPC spec allows both base58 and base64 for the `bytes` field in memcmp filters, and Anchor passes these through directly to the RPC layer.\n\nLet me verify the memory layout one more time: the discriminator takes up 8 bytes at the start, followed by the creator's 32-byte public key, and I can confirm the offsets align correctly with the IDL specification.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8267,"cache_read_input_tokens":53049,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8267},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ea1b77b2-5fe0-46a2-b598-5cd4b215a0f0","uuid":"23acf0ea-3825-4b9a-9f6a-0d476a2a9580"}
